message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Oman in the past 20 years is the death of Sultan Qaboos bin Said Al Said in January 2020 after a long rule of almost 50 years. Sultan Qaboos was the longest-serving leader in the modern Arab world and played a crucial role in transforming Oman into a stable and prosperous nation. His death marked the end of an era and initiated a transition of power to his successor, Sultan Haitham bin Tariq Al Said. This event had a profound impact on Oman's political landscape and its future trajectory.
